  "body": "The extension version of NetworkController has a `destroy` method which [stops the block tracker if it is set](https://github.com/MetaMask/metamask-extension/blob/39f6042e6541e1badb9ee08098e55ce1f3c2dbef/app/scripts/controllers/network/network-controller.ts#L502). This assumes that the controller directly uses a network client that relies directly on `eth-json-rpc-middleware` instead of `web3-provider-engine`, which will be completed via https://github.com/metamask/core/issues/970. \r\n\r\nThis is part of [a larger effort to normalize the API of both network controllers](https://github.com/MetaMask/controllers/issues/971), to make them easier to merge.",
